  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> steak[s]</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into thin wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your<strong> pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Season both sides with <strong>salt</strong> and sprinkle with<strong> half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>coated steak[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated steak[s] </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>cooked steak[s]</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave to rest for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steak[s] are cooking, heat a pot with a lid with a small drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper </strong>and <strong>onion wedges</strong> with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for an initial 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to brown, add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pot with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, remove from the heat and add your<strong> bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the grains are completely coated</p><p>Add 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the bulgur wheat has cooked – this is your <strong>tomatoey bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>remaining roasted garlic paste</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>roasted garlic aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-loin-and-bulgur-bowl-with-roasted-garlic-aioli/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak[s] </strong>finely on a clean board</p><p>Serve the<strong> sliced steak</strong> over the <strong>tomatoey bulgur</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>roasted garlic aioli</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
